               <head>Miscellaneous collection on sectarian polemics and Arabic, 4 items (a-d)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection on sectarian polemics and Arabic, comprising four heterogeneous items from differing sources. Volume not dated. Rough nastaʿlīq. Annotated in margins. Stamped foliation. Binding damaged, boards covered with marbled paper and brown leather edging; marbling delaminating and torn, exposing inner matter (Persian correspondence and Kaithi text). Dimensions of binding are smaller than the text block. Binding broken, detached boards (pale green floral decorative paper edged with brown leather; torn and rubbed). Folios unbound, in order of foliation; minor damage. Condition moderately fragile. Seal erased. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1194-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="18v">ff. 1v-18v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on epistemology by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The work comprises three sections termed guftār. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Crudely illuminated and oxidising sar lawḥ at beginning. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1194-item2">
                     <locus from="19v" to="44r">ff. 19v-44r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Untitled polemic treatise on Shīʿah perspectives regarding the illegitimacy of the <orgName>Umayyad Caliphate</orgName>, by an unnamed author. 
For another copy of the same work, see item c. 

                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Occasional dense annotations in margin. 
</p>
                        <p>Legible shikastah āmīz. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1194-item3">
                     <locus from="46v" to="74v">ff. 46v-74v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on Shīʿah perspectives regarding the illegitimacy of the <orgName>Umayyad Caliphate</orgName>, by an unnamed author. 
For another copy of the same work, see item b. 

                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Occasional dense annotations in margin. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1194-item4">
                     <locus from="76r" to="84v">ff. 76r-84v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Untitled Persian manual on the morphology of Arabic vocabulary by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
